events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen scored a season-high 29 points, Donovan Mitchell had a career-high 14 assists and the Cleveland Cavaliers looked more comfortable back home, holding off the San Antonio Spurs 124-116 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jarrett Allen's 29 points, Donovan Mitchell's 14 assists lift Cavaliers to 124-116 win over Spurs

headlines.description: — Jaden Hardy scored 22 points, Anthony Davis added 15 points and seven rebounds and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Orlando Magic 101-92 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hardy, Davis lead Mavericks past Magic 101-92

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 29 points, one of nine Indiana players in double figures as the Pacers set a franchise record for points in a game in a 162-109 rout of the Washington Wizards on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers rout Wizards 162-109 for most points in NBA franchise history and most allowed by Washington

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 36 points, Davion Mitchell and Andrew Wiggins each added 16 and the Miami Heat beat the Atlanta Hawks 122-112 on Thursday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro scores 36, Heat shake off slow start to beat Hawks 122-112 for 3rd consecutive victory

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: - Josh Giddey made a halfcourt heave at the buzzer to cap perhaps the wildest finish in the NBA this season, giving the Chicago Bulls a 119-117 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on...
headlines.shortLinkText: Josh Giddey's halfcourt heave at the buzzer gives Bulls 119-117 win over the Lakers

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 37 points and Oklahoma City defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 125-104 on Thursday night as the Thunder won their eighth straight and team-record 61st game of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 37 as NBA-leading Thunder beat Grizzlies for team-record 61st victory

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 33 points and 10 rebounds, Amen Thompson finished with 16 points, 10 rebounds and five assists, and the Houston Rockets beat the Utah Jazz 121-110 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alperen Sengun has 33 points and 10 rebounds as Rockets beat Jazz 121-110

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Zach LaVine scored 29 points and Domantas Sabonis finished with 22 points, 19 rebounds and six assists Thursday night to help the Sacramento Kings beat the Portland Trail Blazers 128-107 and snap a four-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zach LaVine, Domantas Sabonis lead Kings to 128-107 win over Trail Blazers
